                <h2>Company or Client Overview for SEO Content Brief</h2>
                <hr class="brief--hr">


                <p>For the successful promotion of a client's project, it is crucial to have a clear understanding of their goals and strategies. This becomes possible through the proper formulation of questions about the project, client needs, as well as products or services. This stage is the foundation for productive collaboration and effective advancement in the field of SEO.</p>

                <h3>Client Information</h3>

                <p>Before starting work on SEO promotion, it's important to gather basic information about the client. This information includes:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Industry:</b> The client's business sector.</li>

                    <li><b>Products/Services:</b> The products or services the client provides.</li>

                    <li><b>Similar Products/Services:</b> Similar products or services already present in the market.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Products/Services</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Brand and Product/Service Description:</b> The client's brand and a description of their products or services.</li>

                    <li><b>Pricing Range and Product Features:</b> The pricing range and specific features of the products.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Contact Persons</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Key Contacts:</b> The importance of communicating with key individuals.</li>

                    <li><b>Contact Information:</b> Contact details for prompt interaction.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Company Activity</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Business Duration:</b> The duration of the business's presence in the market.</li>

                    <li><b>Facilities:</b> Presence of offices, stores, warehouses, and other locations.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Orders and Sales</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Number of Completed Orders:</b> Quantity of orders fulfilled.</li>

                    <li><b>Sales Funnel Description:</b> Description of the sales funnel and ongoing promotions.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Customer Interaction</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Customer Interaction Features:</b> Special aspects of customer interaction.</li>

                    <li><b>Ideal Customer and Typical Customer Problems:</b> Description of the ideal customer and common customer issues.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Projects and Examples</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Completed Projects to Be Proud Of:</b> Orders successfully completed that the company takes pride in.</li>

                    <li><b>List of "Well-Known" Clients, if applicable.</b></li>
                </ul>
                <br><br>

                <h3> Competitive Advantages and Unique Selling Proposition (USP)</h3>

                <p>Understanding the unique attributes of the company, products, or services plays a crucial role in developing a successful SEO strategy. Through in-depth analysis of the USP, several important aspects can be highlighted:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><b>Company Age:</b> The company's history and stability in the market.</li>

                    <li><b>Advantages from Long-Term Experience:</b> Benefits derived from long-term experience.</li>

                    <li><b>Licensing:</b> Possession of necessary licenses and certificates.</li>

                    <li><b>Trust in Licensed Organizations:</b> Trust that clients may have in licensed organizations.</li>

                    <li><b>Production Timelines:</b> Short production timelines as a competitive advantage.</li>

                    <li><b>Flexibility in Meeting Client Needs:</b> Flexibility in responding to client needs.</li>

                    <li><b>Environmental Material:</b> Conscious use of environmentally friendly materials.</li>

                    <li><b>Attracting Environmentally Responsible Clients:</b> Attracting clients valuing a responsible approach to the environment.</li>

                    <li><b>Certifications:</b> Quality product confirmation through relevant certifications.</li>

                    <li><b>Consumer and Partner Trust:</b> Trust from consumers and partners.</li>

                    <li><b>Official Representatives:</b> Benefits of working with official representatives.</li>

                    <li><b>Access to Exclusive Terms and Products:</b> Access to exclusive terms and products.</li>

                    <li><b>Delivery/Installation/Disassembly/Service:</b> Integrated service from start to finish.</li>

                    <li><b>Customer Convenience, Elimination of Additional Hassles:</b> Convenience for clients, freeing them from additional concerns.</li>

                    <li><b>Individual Approach:</b> Personalized service and solutions.</li>

                    <li><b>Satisfaction of Unique Customer Needs:</b> Satisfaction of the unique needs of each client.</li>

                    <li><b>Low Prices:</b> Direct factory deliveries for guaranteed low prices.</li>

                    <li><b>Attraction of Price-Sensitive Clients:</b> Attraction of price-sensitive clients.</li>

                    <li><b>Fast Delivery:</b> Efficient delivery system to meet urgent needs.</li>

                    <li><b>Increased Customer Satisfaction with Service Speed:</b> Increased customer satisfaction with service speed.</li>

                    <li><b>Convenient Payment:</b> Flexible and convenient payment systems for clients.</li>

                    <li><b>Additional Comfort in Collaboration:</b> Creation of additional comfort in the collaboration process.</li>

                    <li><b>Warranty:</b> Provision of long-term warranties as a sign of trust.</li>

                    <li><b>Protection of Customer Interests in the Long Term:</b> Protection of customer interests in the long term.</li>

                    <li><b>Discount System:</b> Attraction and retention of regular clients through advantageous discount programs.</li>

                    <li><b>Encouragement of Repeat Orders and Loyalty:</b> Encouragement of repeat orders and loyalty.</li>

                    <li><b>Wide Range:</b> Diversity of products or services.</li>

                    <li><b>Satisfaction of Various Customer Needs:</b> Satisfaction of various customer needs.</li>

                    <li><b>Rich Color Palette:</b> Aesthetics and visually appealing characteristics of products.</li>

                    <li><b>Choice from a Variety of Colors:</b> The opportunity to choose from a variety of colors.</li>

                    <li><b>Quality:</b> Confirmation of high product quality through numerous certificates.</li>

                    <li><b>Establishment of Standards and Attraction of Quality-Oriented Clients:</b> Establishment of standards and attraction of quality-oriented clients.</li>

                    <li><b>Consultations:</b> Free consultations as an additional service.</li>

                    <li><b>Establishment of Trusting Relationships with Clients:</b> Establishment of trusting relationships with clients.</li>

                    <li><b>Qualified Experts:</b> Presence of qualified specialists in the team.</li>

                    <li><b>Ensuring High Professionalism in Service Provision:</b> Ensuring a high level of professionalism in service provision.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>By emphasizing these competitive advantages in the SEO brief, we create a foundation for a successful promotion strategy, highlighting the client's uniqueness in the market.</p>


                <h3>Regional Audience Coverage and Past SEO Work</h3>

                <h4>Audience Coverage</h4>

                <p>Adapting the strategy to the characteristics of different regions and cities is crucial for successful promotion, especially when scaling the business. Considering this factor, it is necessary to determine the focus locations and address the issue of website multilingualism in case of expansion beyond one country.</p>

                <h4>Past SEO Work</h4>

                <p>It's important to find out whether previous optimization work has been carried out on the website. Consider the following aspects:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Completed Work:</strong> Determine the tasks conducted within the site, including technical optimization and content optimization.</li>

                    <li><strong>Timeline and Suspension:</strong> Clarify the timeline of the performed work and, if possible, the reasons for any suspension.</li>

                    <li><strong>Backlink Acquisition:</strong> Check if there was any backlink acquisition for site promotion.</li>

                    <li><strong>Previous Service Provider Data:</strong> Obtain information about the last service provider involved in promotion and their approach.</li>

                    <li><strong>SEO Reports:</strong> If available, request the latest reports on site positions, keyword research, and metrics.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Site Description</h3>

                <h4>Content Management System (CMS) and Access</h4>

                <p>For effective interaction with the site, provide the following information:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>CMS:</strong> Specify the CMS used for the site.</li>

                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> Provide access to the site's admin panel, web analytics, and other tools.</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Hosting Access</h4>

                <p>To ensure the site's seamless operation and perform technical tasks, provide access to the site's hosting, including FTP access data.</p>

                <h3>Website Content</h3>

                <h4>Material Submission</h4>

                <p>For effective website content and optimization, specify:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Texts:</strong> Availability of unique texts for the site and the possibility of rewriting if needed.</li>

                    <a class="chips" target="_blank" href="/pages/writing/website-content.php"> How to write website content  brief </a>

                    <li><strong>Images:</strong> Provide high-quality original photos for design and content.</li>
                    <a class="chips" target="_blank" href="/pages/graphic/graphic.php"> How to write graphic design brief </a>

                    <li><strong>Videos:</strong> Presence of video content for the site.</li>
                    <a class="chips" target="_blank" href="/pages/video/video.php"> How to write video brief </a>

                </ul>

                <h4>Price Publication</h4>

                <p><strong>Prices:</strong> Are there plans to publish prices on the site, including product prices, promotions, and downloadable price lists.</p>

                <h3>Inspiring Examples (Continuation)</h3>

                <h4>Interesting Websites:</h4>

                <p>Ask the client to specify websites they find inspiring. This may include the presentation style, content, the way materials are displayed, and the types of materials used, such as texts, images, or videos.</p>

                <p>This information will allow for a more accurate adaptation of your website's content and design to the expectations and preferences of the target audience. Also, by examining successful examples, you can identify elements that are effective for your niche and business model.</p>

                <h3>Technical Details</h3>

                <h4>Requirements for Technical Solutions</h4>

                <p>Determine the requirements for technical solutions on the website:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Integrations:</strong> Is there a need for integrations with other services or platforms?</li>

                    <li><strong>Efficiency:</strong> Are specific technical solutions required to ensure high performance and security?</li>

                    <li><strong>Mobile Compatibility:</strong> Is mobile compatibility of the site important?</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Testing and Maintenance</h4>

                <p>Specify information about plans for testing and maintaining the site:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Testing:</strong> Are there plans for testing the functionality, compatibility, and security of the site before and after launch?</li>

                    <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> What measures are taken for regular maintenance and updating of the site after its launch?</li>
                </ul>

                <p>This information will help create a more detailed and effective development and promotion plan for your web project.</p>








                <br><br>










                <h2>Goals and KPI </h2>

                <hr class="brief--hr">

                <h3>Project Goals and Key Performance Indicators (KPI)</h3>

                <p>Comprehending the objectives of a project constitutes a crucial phase for ensuring its triumphant promotion. The delineation of goals can be categorized into two primary domains: informational and commercial, each strategically oriented towards attaining distinct and measurable outcomes. This multifaceted approach aids in not only elucidating the purpose of the project but also in crafting targeted strategies tailored to meet the diverse objectives within the spectrum of information dissemination and business expansion.</p>

                <h3>Informational Goals</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Company and Products/Services Information:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Brief introduction to the company's activities and offered products/services.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Visitor engagement level, time spent on the site.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Self-Exploration of Products/Services by Visitors:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Provide visitors with the opportunity for in-depth exploration of the company's range.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Frequency and duration of visits to product/service pages.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Brand Recognition and Image Enhancement:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Create, strengthen, or change the company's image and brand.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Growth in brand recognition, positive reviews, and reputation.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Promotion of Company/Product/Service/Brand:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Actively promote the company and its offerings.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Increase in traffic, conversions through marketing channels.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Educational Objectives:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Provide visitors with educational content about products/services.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Level of information assimilation, engagement in educational sections.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Feedback Collection:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Provide technical consultation, respond to inquiries.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Number of inquiries, response time to feedback.</p>
                </ul>

                <h3>Commercial Goals</h3>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Attraction of End Consumers:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Capture attention and convert visitors into customers.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Conversions on product pages, registrations, purchases.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Attraction of New Partners/Dealers:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Expand the network of partners and dealers.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Number of new partner applications, successful deals.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Service Provision:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Provide various services upon customer requests.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Volume and quality of provided services.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Order Placement/Booking:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Visitors placing orders or booking services.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Number of orders placed, successful bookings.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Purchases:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Increase sales volume.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Total sales volume, average order value.</p>

                    <li>
                        <h3>Interaction with Existing Dealers and Partners:</h3>
                    </li>
                    <p><b>Goal:</b> Strengthen relationships with existing dealers and partners.</p>
                    <p><b>KPI:</b> Satisfaction level, feedback, volume of joint projects.</p>
                </ul>

                <p>When formulating an SEO strategy and content plan, consider these goals and KPIs to effectively build a path to achieve the set objectives.</p>





